	<div class="bio-content">
		<h2>Patrick Wilmot</h2>
		<p>Patrick Wilmot was born February 21, 1989 in Roswell, Ga where his family still lives in the same house. His father Lee Wilmot raced Shelby Mustangs and Trans Am Mustangs in the Historic Sportscar Series in the late 1980's and early 1990's. Patrick has been around cars and racing his entire life but didn't decide to start racing until he was 16. He entered the ProCup karting league at Andretti Indoor Karting at 17 quickly moving up to outdoor endurance karting and eventually into the #18 BenchWarmers Mustang in SCCA. Patrick is now the lead instructor for the ProCup Karting League at Andretti Indoor Karting where he teaches young aspiring racers the basics of karting. With several track records and 7 years of karting experience he is the face of the league and their karting camp.
		<h2>Wilmot Racing</h2>
		<p>Wilmot Racing was created in 2009 by the Wilmot family. The team consists of: Driver- Patrick Wilmot, Crew Chief/Father- Lee Wilmot, Photographer- Ross Monckton, and the crew- Kitty Wilmot(Mother), Don Wilmot(Uncle), and close friend Jeff Mills. Wilmot Racing crews an American Sedan Mustang in the SafeRacer SCCA National Racing Series. In 2009 the team finished second in the Southeast for Regionals and in 2010 third in the Southeast for Nationals. With 5 National victories and dozens of podiums the team has had an outstanding showing for their first few years in racing.
		</p>
	</div>
